<% @page_title = "Glossary" %>

<dl>
	<dt>Global Id</dt>
		<dd>A Player's Public Key. The universal identifier. It does not assist in resolution and not mentioned in the app.</dd>
	<dt>Peer (Model)</dt>
		<dd>A Player discovers and interacts with other Players through their Peer records.</dd>
	<dt>Player (Model)</dt>
		<dd>A Player is an agent rooted in the local server. May be human, animal, mineral or automaton.</dd>
	<dt>Resolver (Model)</dt>
		<dd>Resolver records record the Global Id and resolution end point of Peers.</dd>
	<dt>Transport (Model)</dt>
		<dd>Transport addresses belong to Players and are discoverable by Peers. They are the functioning addresses from other schemes, for example: email, web, telephone, carrier pigeon.</dd>
	<dt>Resolution (a process)</dt>
		<dd>Gets the public key from a Peer Url (e.g. <%= get_peer_url(:id => Player.first.signifier, :only_path => false ) %>).</dd>
</dl>
